{
  "doc_id": "57396",
  "text": "We previously showed PCPE-1 RNA to be expressed within developing vascular tissues [CITATION_1] , while others have shown that PCPE-1 expression may be involved in inhibiting the growth properties of vascular smooth muscle cells [CITATION_2] . In fact, it has been suggested that PCPE-1 may be involved in a more general control of cell growth, as disruption of the PCPE-1 gene Pcolce can induce the anchorage-independent growth of cultured fibroblasts [CITATION_3] ). It has also been shown that PCPE-1 may be necessary for lumen formation in a model of in vitro angiogenesis, although this effect may be secondary to the role of PCPE-1 in collagen biosynthesis [CITATION_4] .",
